result.name: Thai Chiu

reviews.text: Thai Chiu is a food gem in Sham Shui Po. This Michelin-recommended eatery is consistently delicious, and staff are friendly and welcoming. There are vegetarian-friendly options available, so everyone can find something tasty to eat. Try the Pad Thai for a dish that's not only delicious, but looks awesome, too.
Just good food, good ingredients, I eat well there 2-3 times a week. Tastes great too and friendly.
Decent enough Thai food. I got the yellow curry. The curry had some flavor. The potatoes in the curry were sad and flavorless, though.
Really great Thai food. The thai green curry is excellent and serving portions are big! Amazing value for money!

Terrible pad thai... not only comes soaked in a kind of soup, but also suuuuuuper salty... Actually all the food was super salty. They brag about Michelin guide recomendation.... Thumbs down, Horrible experience. We left without eating.

Thai Chiu is a food gem in Sham Shui Po. This Michelin-recommended eatery is consistently delicious, and staff are friendly and welcoming. There are vegetarian-friendly options available, so everyone can find something tasty to eat. Try the Pad Thai for a dish that's not only delicious, but looks awesome, too.
可能熱天関係，食物未能保持新鮮，例如雲吞已開始有變壞味道，飲品沒有水準，唯服務態度尚好。
Just good food, good ingredients, I eat well there 2-3 times a week. Tastes great too and friendly.
